1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,640
All right, Crawl here again for our final chapter.

2
00:00:04,640 --> 00:00:12,880
Because suretyship is architected as a no-loss contract where recovery must be guaranteed, the underwriting process is exacting.

3
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:23,359
Tariff premium rates are determined strictly by the bond's hazard classification, ranging from Class 1 up to Class 5.

4
00:00:23,359 --> 00:00:36,640
To evaluate an applicant safely, underwriters rely on the Three C's. One, Character: This measures the credibility, integrity, and market reputation of the principal.

5
00:00:36,640 --> 00:00:49,440
Underwriters verify if management figures are listed on the Insurance Commission's negative list, look for past defaults, and check for active lawsuits regarding misappropriation of funds.

6
00:00:49,440 --> 00:01:08,720
Two, Capacity: This measures the operational capability and expertise of the applicant. Underwriters analyze whether their current technical facilities, equipment, and active workloads will allow them to successfully execute the contract.

7
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:29,840
Three, Capital: This evaluates financial strength. Underwriters dissect audited financial statements for the past two years, tracking the liquidity ratio to measure cash conversion, the debt ratio to calculate creditor exposure, and the debt-to-equity ratio to measure leverage.

8
00:01:29,840 --> 00:01:38,799
When an application presents higher risk, a surety will protect its exposure by demanding acceptable collateral.

9
00:01:38,799 --> 00:01:45,759
This is subject to rigid legal guidelines. Cash remains the absolute standard.

10
00:01:45,759 --> 00:02:00,159
Government securities must carry a maturity period of no more than one year, be free of encumbrances, and require a formal deed of assignment alongside physical deposit of the original certificates.

11
00:02:00,159 --> 00:02:08,160
Savings or time deposits must match the full face value of the bond and require an officially acknowledged bank assignment.

12
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:22,239
Stock certificates must be non-speculative blue chips, hold a market value at least twice the amount of the bond, and have the lien formally recorded in the issuing corporation's books.

13
00:02:22,239 --> 00:02:41,360
Real estate mortgages must be prime residential or commercial properties registered directly to the principal, completely free of encumbrances, and worth at least twice the value of the bond, with the mortgage legally annotated on the title before any bond instrument is signed and released.

14
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:53,120
You must execute a final compliance check. Verify that all corporate signatories are legally authorized via a valid secretary's certificate or board resolution.

15
00:02:51,360 --> 00:03:03,920
Confirm that all original collateral documents are physically secured and ensure that any matching reinsurance slips are fully executed and co-terminous with the bond term.

16
00:03:01,440 --> 00:03:14,599
Managing risk means maintaining absolute clarity through every line of the contract. Drill into the Three C's, enforce proper documentation, and protect the integrity of the transaction.